The Armed Forces of Nigeria has through the Air Component of Operation GAMA AIKI neutralized some bandits at their hideout located about 10km Southeast of Pandogari in Niger State. The acting director Defence Media Operations, Brig. General Benard Onyeuko said the operation was undertaken on 31 March 2020 in continuation of air operations aimed at flushing out armed bandits from the country. He said the airstrike followed credible human intelligence reports indicating that the bandits had assembled under a group of trees at Kalaibu Village near Pandogari. “A Nigerian Air Force attack helicopter dispatched for an armed reconnaissance mission in the area spotted and engaged the bandits, neutralizing some, while others managed to escape with gunshot wounds,” he said.